{"title_page": "Basdorf", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=September 2011}}\n\n{{Infobox German location\n|name             = Basdorf\n|German_name      = \n|type              = Ortsteil\n|Municipality = [[Wandlitz]]\n|image_photo      = \n|imagesize        = \n|image_caption    = \n|image_coa           = Wappen Basdorf (Wandlitz).png\n|image_flag       = \n|coordinates      = {{coord|52|43|3|N|13|26|7.44|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|image_plan         =\n|plantext =\n|state       = Brandenburg\n|region = \n|district        = Barnim\n|elevation                      = 58-69\n|area           = 13.35\n|population        = 5274\n|Stand            = 2010-12-31\n|postal_code              = 16348\n|area_code          = 033397 \n|licence              = BAR \n|Gemeindeschl\u00fcssel= \n|divisions       = \n|website          = \n|year             = \n|_noautocat       = \n}}\n\n'''Basdorf''' is a village to the north of [[Berlin]], in the German federal state of [[Brandenburg]]. Until 2003, when it merged into [[Wandlitz]], it was an autonomous municipality.\n\n[[Category:Villages in Brandenburg]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities in Brandenburg]]\n\n\n{{Brandenburg-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=September 2011}}\n\n{{Infobox German location\n|name             = Basdorf\n|German_name      = \n|type              = Ortsteil\n|Municipality = [[Wandlitz]]\n|image_photo      = \n|imagesize        = \n|image_caption    = \n|image_coa           = Wappen Basdorf (Wandlitz).png\n|Wappengr\u00f6\u00dfe      = \n|image_flag       = \n|coordinates      = {{coord|52|43|3|N|13|26|7.44|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|Karte            =\n|image_plan         =\n|plantext =\n|state       = Brandenburg\n|region = \n|district        = Barnim\n|Amt = |Gemeindeverwaltungsverband = |Samtgemeinde = \n|Verbandsgemeinde =  |Verwaltungsgemeinschaft = |Verwaltungsverband = \n|elevation                      = 58\n|H\u00f6he-bis                  = 69\n|H\u00f6he-Bezug                = DE-NN\n|elevationmax     = 69\n|area           = 13.35\n|area_metro       = \n|population        = 5274\n|Stand            = 2010-12-31\n|pop_metro        = \n|postal_code              = 16348\n|PLZ-alt          = \n|area_code          = 033397 \n|licence              = BAR \n|Gemeindeschl\u00fcssel= \n|NUTS             = \n|LOCODE           = \n|divisions       = \n|website          = \n|mayor    = Peter Liebehenschel\n|B\u00fcrgermeistertitel = \n|party           = \n|ruling_party1    = |ruling_party2  =  |ruling_party3 = \n|year             = \n|_noautocat       = \n}}\n\n'''Basdorf''' is a village to the north of [[Berlin]], in the German federal state of [[Brandenburg]]. Since 2003 it was an autonomous municipality, merged in [[Wandlitz]].\n\n[[Category:Villages in Brandenburg]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities in Brandenburg]]\n\n\n{{Brandenburg-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basdorf"}
{"title_page": "Raffaele Nuzzo", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Raffaele Nuzzo\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1973|2|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Monza]], Italy\n| height      = 1.89 m\n| position    = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 = [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]]\n| years1      = 1991\u20132000 | clubs1 = [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]] | caps1 = 1  | goals1 = 0\n| years2      = 1992\u20131994 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[U.S. Pergocrema 1932|Pergocrema]] (loan)  | caps2 = 2  | goals2 = 0\n| years3      = 1994\u20131995 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[A.S. Fasano|Fasano]] (loan)               | caps3 = 26 | goals3 = 0\n| years4      = 1995\u20131996 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]] (loan)      | caps4 = 2  | goals4 = 0\n| years5      = 1996\u20131997 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[A.S. Gualdo Calcio|Gualdo]] (loan)        | caps5 = 17 | goals5 = 0\n| years6      = 1999      | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] (loan) | caps6 = 0  | goals6 = 0\n| years7      = 2000\u20132007 | clubs7 = [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]]               | caps7 = 84 | goals7 = 0\n| years8      = 2001 | clubs8 = \u2192 [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] (loan)    | caps8 = 0  | goals8 = 0\n| totalcaps   = 132\n| totalgoals  = 0\n}}\n\n'''Raffaele Nuzzo''' (born 21 February 1973) is a Italian former professional [[association football|footballer]]. He spent most of his career in the Italian [[Serie C1]] and [[Serie C2]], in the role of a backup [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Internazionale===\nBorn in 1973, in [[Monza]], which at the time was in the [[Province of Milan]] (now in the [[Province of Monza and Brianza]]), Nuzzo started his professional career at [[F.C. Internazionale Milano]], one of the major Italian clubs of the region, initially joining the team's youth side.\n\nSince the 1992 season, he spent his career on loan at various [[Serie C2]] clubs, as Internazionale had more experienced players as their second goalkeeper, such as [[Beniamino Abate]], [[Luca Mondini]], [[Marco Landucci]] and [[Andrea Mazzantini]]. He played 26 out of 34 league matches for [[A.S. Fasano|Fasano]], and his performances secured him a move to [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]], a team with the aim of obtaining promotion to [[Serie C1]]. He played 2 matches for the Serie C2 runners-up, but the club failed to obtain promotion as they lost in the playoffs. The following season, he moved to [[A.S. Gualdo Calcio|Gualdo]] of [[Serie C1]], which had finished in fifth place the previous season. Due to the departure of [[Davide Torchia]] and [[Oscar Verderame]], he became one of the team's first choice keepers, along with the more experienced [[Marco Savorani]]. Although Gualdo finished just above the relegation zone, Nuzzo's performances earned him a place in Internazionale's first team, as third goalkeeper behind [[Andrea Mazzantini]], but ahead of the young youth products. He was on the bench for the second leg of the club's victorious [[1994 UEFA Cup Final]] ([[Beniamino Abate]] was on the bench for the first leg). In the [[1998\u201399 Serie A|1998\u201399 season]], Internazionale signed [[S\u00e9bastien Frey]], which led to Mazzantini's departure from the club in the January transfer window, while Nuzzo remained as the team's third-choice keeper. He played his only match in [[Serie A]] and for Internazionale on the last matchday of the Serie A season, on 23 May 1999, when he came on as a substitute for starting goalkeeper [[Gianluca Pagliuca]] in the last minute of Inter's match against [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]], with the score 2\u20131; the match ended in a 3\u20131 victory for Inter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interfc.it/Scheda.asp?id=150|title=Raffaele NUZZO|publisher=Inter F.C.|language=Italian|accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn June 1999, Nuzzo left for [[FA Premier League]] side [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] on loan, along with [[Antonio Caruso]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football-kharine-moves-to-celtic-1101935.html|title=Football: Kharine moves to Celtic|publisher=[[The Independent]] | location=London | first=Kieran | last=Daley|date=23 June 1999|accessdate=9 January 2010}}</ref> Following [[Steve Ogrizovic]]'s recovery from injury, who was originally the team's second goalkeeper, Nuzzo was sent back to Internazionale in November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football-fulham-close-to-completing-hughes-deal-1127252.html|title=Football: Fulham close to completing Hughes deal|publisher=[[The Independent]] | location=London | first=Alan | last=Nixon|date=19 November 1999|accessdate=9 January 2010}}</ref> His only Coventry appearance was one to forget. It came in the [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] against [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]], as the second tier team trounced their Premier League opponents 5\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sportinglife.com/football/cc_championship/coventry/reports/story_get.cgi?STORY_NAME=soccer/99/09/14/SOCCER_Tranmere_Nightlead.html&TEAMHD=coventry&DIV=nat1&TEAM=COVENTRY--CITY&RH=Coventry--City&PREV_SEASON=1998&BID=|title=Tranmere 5 Coventry 1|publisher=Sporting Life|date=14 September 1999|accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Reggiana===\nAfter he returned from England, Nuzzo was signed by [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]] in January 2000. In his first season with the team, he played as a backup to [[Mirko Bellodi]] and [[Beniamino Abate]], replacing the recently departed [[Alberto Maria Fontana]]. In his second season with the team, he played as [[Lorenzo Squizzi]]'s backup. As the club also had [[Andrea Artich]] and [[Michele Nicoletti]], he left for England again in February 2001, joining [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,,11682_2204095,00+en-USS_01DBC.html|title=GED BID ACCEPTED|date=14 February 2001|accessdate=9 January 2010|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/w/wigan_athletic/1194674.stm|title=Rioch bust-up riddle|date=28 February 2001|accessdate=9 January 2010|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> but did not make a single first team appearance for the club.\n\nHe returned to Reggiana in the 2001\u201302 season, where he continued to serve as the team's backup goalkeeper, for [[Patrick Bettoni]]. In 2002\u201303 season, however, he played as the team's first choice keeper, ahead of [[Luca Mondini]], making 19 appearances. The following season, however, Mondini was restored as the team's first choice keeper. In the 2004\u201305 season, [[Gabriele Paoletti]] succeed Mondini as Reggiana's first choice keeper, and Nuzzo played one match for the team throughout the season, which ultimately ended in relegation to Serie C2 in 2005.\n\nIn his final years with club, he finally became the team's first choice keeper, as the club had only signed the inexperienced [[Davide Bagnacani]] as an additional goalkeeper, who had recently graduated from [[Piacenza Calcio]]'s youth system.\n\nAfter the club lost in the promotion playoffs in 2007, Nuzzo retired from professional football. He was replaced by [[Marco Ambrosio]] and [[Luca Tomasig]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{TuttoCalciatori|Nuzzo_Raffaele}}\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*[http://archivio.inter.it/cgi-bin/giocatori-scheda?codice=G0455&L=en Inter Archive]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nuzzo, Raffaele}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Monza]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Italian footballers]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Inter Milan players]]\n[[Category:A.S. Livorno Calcio players]]\n[[Category:Coventry City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Reggio Audace F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wigan Athletic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriate sportspeople in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Italian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:UEFA Cup winning players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Raffaele Nuzzo\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1973|2|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Monza]], Italy\n| height              = 1.89 m\n| position            = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1         =\n| youthclubs1         = [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]]\n| years1              = 1991\u20132000 | clubs1 = [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]] | caps1 = 1  | goals1 = 0\n| years2              = 1992\u20131994 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[U.S. Pergocrema 1932|Pergocrema]] (loan)  | caps2 = 2  | goals2 = 0\n| years3              = 1994\u20131995 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[A.S. Fasano|Fasano]] (loan)               | caps3 = 26 | goals3 = 0\n| years4              = 1995\u20131996 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]] (loan)      | caps4 = 2  | goals4 = 0\n| years5              = 1996\u20131997 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[A.S. Gualdo Calcio|Gualdo]] (loan)        | caps5 = 17 | goals5 = 0\n| years6              = 1999      | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] (loan) | caps6 = 0  | goals6 = 0\n| years7              = 2000\u20132007 | clubs7 = [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]]               | caps7 = 84 | goals7 = 0\n| years8              = 2001 | clubs8 = \u2192 [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] (loan)    | caps8 = 0  | goals8 = 0\n| totalcaps           = 132\n| totalgoals          = 0\n}}\n\n'''Raffaele Nuzzo''' (born 21 February 1973) is a former [[Italians|Italian]] [[association football|footballer]]. He spent most of his career in the Italian [[Serie C1]] and [[Serie C2]], in the role of a backup [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Internazionale===\nBorn in 1973, in [[Monza]], which at the time was in the [[Province of Milan]] (now in the [[Province of Monza and Brianza]]), Nuzzo started his professional career at [[F.C. Internazionale Milano]], one of the major Italian clubs of the region, initially joining the team's youth side.\n\nSince the 1992 season, he spent his career on loan at various [[Serie C2]] clubs, as Internazionale had more experienced players as their second goalkeeper, such as [[Beniamino Abate]], [[Luca Mondini]], [[Marco Landucci]] and [[Andrea Mazzantini]]. He played 26 out of 34 league matches for [[A.S. Fasano|Fasano]], and his performances secured him a move to [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]], a team with the aim of obtaining promotion to [[Serie C1]]. He played 2 matches for the Serie C2 runners-up, but the club failed to obtain promotion as they lost in the playoffs. The following season, he moved to [[A.S. Gualdo Calcio|Gualdo]] of [[Serie C1]], which had finished in fifth place the previous season. Due to the departure of [[Davide Torchia]] and [[Oscar Verderame]], he became one of the team's first choice keepers, along with the more experienced [[Marco Savorani]]. Although Gualdo finished just above the relegation zone, Nuzzo's performances earned him a place in Internazionale's first team, as third goalkeeper behind [[Andrea Mazzantini]], but ahead of the young youth products. He was on the bench for the second leg of the club's victorious [[1994 UEFA Cup Final]] ([[Beniamino Abate]] was on the bench for the first leg). In the [[1998\u201399 Serie A|1998\u201399 season]], Internazionale signed [[S\u00e9bastien Frey]], which led to Mazzantini's departure from the club in the January transfer window, while Nuzzo remained as the team's third-choice keeper. He played his only match in [[Serie A]] and for Internazionale on the last matchday of the Serie A season, on 23 May 1999, when he came on as a substitute for starting goalkeeper [[Gianluca Pagliuca]] in the last minute of Inter's match against [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]], with the score 2\u20131; the match ended in a 3\u20131 victory for Inter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interfc.it/Scheda.asp?id=150|title=Raffaele NUZZO|publisher=Inter F.C.|language=Italian|accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn June 1999, Nuzzo left for [[FA Premier League]] side [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] on loan, along with [[Antonio Caruso]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football-kharine-moves-to-celtic-1101935.html|title=Football: Kharine moves to Celtic|publisher=[[The Independent]] | location=London | first=Kieran | last=Daley|date=23 June 1999|accessdate=9 January 2010}}</ref> Following [[Steve Ogrizovic]]'s recovery from injury, who was originally the team's second goalkeeper, Nuzzo was sent back to Internazionale in November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football-fulham-close-to-completing-hughes-deal-1127252.html|title=Football: Fulham close to completing Hughes deal|publisher=[[The Independent]] | location=London | first=Alan | last=Nixon|date=19 November 1999|accessdate=9 January 2010}}</ref> His only Coventry appearance was one to forget. It came in the [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] against [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]], as the second tier team trounced their Premier League opponents 5\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sportinglife.com/football/cc_championship/coventry/reports/story_get.cgi?STORY_NAME=soccer/99/09/14/SOCCER_Tranmere_Nightlead.html&TEAMHD=coventry&DIV=nat1&TEAM=COVENTRY--CITY&RH=Coventry--City&PREV_SEASON=1998&BID=|title=Tranmere 5 Coventry 1|publisher=Sporting Life|date=14 September 1999|accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Reggiana===\nAfter he returned from England, Nuzzo was signed by [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]] in January 2000. In his first season with the team, he played as a backup to [[Mirko Bellodi]] and [[Beniamino Abate]], replacing the recently departed [[Alberto Maria Fontana]]. In his second season with the team, he played as [[Lorenzo Squizzi]]'s backup. As the club also had [[Andrea Artich]] and [[Michele Nicoletti]], he left for England again in February 2001, joining [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,,11682_2204095,00+en-USS_01DBC.html|title=GED BID ACCEPTED|date=14 February 2001|accessdate=9 January 2010|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/w/wigan_athletic/1194674.stm|title=Rioch bust-up riddle|date=28 February 2001|accessdate=9 January 2010|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> but did not make a single first team appearance for the club.\n\nHe returned to Reggiana in the 2001\u201302 season, where he continued to serve as the team's backup goalkeeper, for [[Patrick Bettoni]]. In 2002\u201303 season, however, he played as the team's first choice keeper, ahead of [[Luca Mondini]], making 19 appearances. The following season, however, Mondini was restored as the team's first choice keeper. In the 2004\u201305 season, [[Gabriele Paoletti]] succeed Mondini as Reggiana's first choice keeper, and Nuzzo played one match for the team throughout the season, which ultimately ended in relegation to Serie C2 in 2005.\n\nIn his final years with club, he finally became the team's first choice keeper, as the club had only signed the inexperienced [[Davide Bagnacani]] as an additional goalkeeper, who had recently graduated from [[Piacenza Calcio]]'s youth system.\n\nAfter the club lost in the promotion playoffs in 2007, Nuzzo retired from professional football. He was replaced by [[Marco Ambrosio]] and [[Luca Tomasig]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{TuttoCalciatori|Nuzzo_Raffaele}}\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*[http://archivio.inter.it/cgi-bin/giocatori-scheda?codice=G0455&L=en Inter Archive]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nuzzo, Raffaele}}\n[[Category:Italian footballers]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Inter Milan players]]