 about bears]]\n[[Category:2010s coming-of-age drama films]]\n[[Category:2012 directorial debut films]]\n", "name_user": "176.236.110.139", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brave_(2012_film)"}
{"title_page": "Se\u00e1n O'Brien (Tipperary hurler)", "text_new": "{{infobox GAA player\n|image           =\n|name            = Sean O'Brien \n|irish           = Se\u00e1n \u00d3 Briain\n|nickname        =\n|occupation      = Engineer\n|height          =\n|sport           = Hurling\n|code            = Hurling\n|county          = Tipperary\n|province        = Munster\n|club            = [[Newport GAA|Newport]]\n|clyears         = \n|clposition      = Corner back\n|clapps(points)  =\n|clcounty        = 0\n|clprovince      =\n|clallireland    =\n|colleges        = [[University of Limerick]]\n|fitz            = 0\n|colyears        = 2007-2012\n|counties        = [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n|icyears         = 2017\u2013present\n|icposition      = Left corner-back\n|icapps(points)  = 7 (0-01)\n|icprovince      = 0\n|icallireland    = 1\n\n|nhl             = 0\n|allstars        = 0\n|clupdate        =\n|icupdate        = 10:37, 19 June 2019\n| birth_date= 1990\n| birth_place=[[Newport, County Tipperary|Newport]], [[County Tipperary]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n}}\n'''Sean O'Brien ''' (born 1990) is an Irish [[hurling|hurler]] who plays for Tipperary Championship club [[Newport GAA|Newport]] and at inter-county level with the [[Tipperary senior hurling team]]. He usually lines out as a left corner-back.\n\n==Playing career==\n===University of Limerick===\n\nO'Brien studied at the [[University of Limerick]] between 2007 and 2012 and joined the senior hurling team in his second year. He was a regular playedin several [[Fitzgibbon Cup]] campaigns with the university.\n\n===Newport===\n\nO'Brien joined the [[Newport GAA|Newport]] club at a young age and played in all grades at juvenile and underage levels. He eventually joined the club's top adult team in the [[Tipperary Intermediate Hurling Championship|Tipperary Intermediate Championship]].\n\nOn 23 October 2016, O'Brien captained Newport in the Tipperary Intermediate Championship final against [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]]. He ended the game with a winners' medal following the 1-17 to 0-15 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/newport-more-than-a-team-this-is-a-family-436795.html|title=Newport: More than a team \u2014 this is a family|publisher=Irish Examiner|date=28 December 2016|accessdate=18 June 2019|first=Larry|last=Ryan}}</ref>\n\n===Tipperary===\n====Minor and under-21====\n\nO'Brien first played for [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] when he joined the minor team in advance of the [[2007 All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship#Munster Minor Hurling Championship|2007 Munster Championship]]. He made his first appearance for the team on 2 May 2007 when he lined out at right corner-back in a 3-12 to 1-11 defeat of [[Clare GAA|Clare]]. O'Brien was switched to left corner-back when Tipperary faced [[Cork GAA|Cork]] in the [[Munster Minor Hurling Championship|Munster final]] on 8 July 2007. He ended the game with a winners' medal following the 0-18 to 1-11 victory. On 2 September 2007, O'Brien won an [[All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship|All-Ireland]] medal from left corner-back following Tipperary's 4-14 to 2-11 defeat of Cork in the [[2007 All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship#All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship|All-Ireland final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/hurling/carey-fires-tipperary-to-double-minor-glory-26315499.html|title=Carey fires Tipperary to double minor glory|date=3 September 2007|publisher=Irish Independent|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=|last=}}</ref>\n\nO'Brien was again eligible for the Tipperary minor team in [[2008 All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship#Munster Minor Hurling Championship|2008]]. He was an unused substitute when Tipperary suffered a 0-19 to 0-18 defeat by Cork in the Munster final on 13 July 2008.\n\nO'Brien was drafted onto the Tipperary under-21 team for the [[2010 All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship#Munster Under-21 Hurling Championship|2010 Munster Championship]]. He won a [[Munster Under-21 Hurling Championship|Munster Championship]] medal as a non-playing substitute on 28 July 2010 following Tipperary's 1-22 to 0-17 defeat of Cork in the final.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/tipp-take-another-step-forward-126466.html|title=Tipp take another step forward|date=29 June 2010|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Fintan|last=O'Toole}}</ref> On 11 September 2010, O'Brien won an [[All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship|All-Ireland]] medal from the substitutes' bench following Tipperary's 5-22 to 0-12 defeat of [[Galway GAA|Galway]] in the [[2010 All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship Final|All-Ireland final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/hurling/fivestar-tipp-cruise-to-title-26680149.html|title=Five-star Tipp cruise to title|date=12 September 2010|publisher=Irish Independent|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Damian|last=Lawlor}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 June 2011, O'Brien made his first appearance for the Tipperary under-21 team when he came on as a substitute for [[James Barry (hurler)|James Barry]] at centre-back in a 4-12 to 1-16 defeat of [[Waterford GAA|Waterford]]. He was switched to left corner-back for the 4-19 to 1-21 defeat by Cork on 15 July 2011.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/awesome-rebel-firepower-161308.html|title=Awesome Rebel firepower|date=16 July 2011|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Fintan|last=O'Toole}}</ref>\n\n====Intermediate====\n\nO'Brien was added to the Tipperary intermediate panel for the [[2010 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship#Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|2010 Munster Championship]]. He was an unused substitute on 30 May 2010 when Tipperary suffered a 1-18 to 1-12 defeat by Cork at the quarter-final stage.\n\nOn 9 June 2013, O'Brien made his first appearance for the intermediate team when he lined out at right corner-back in a 0-20 to 0-15 defeat of Cork.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/hammersley-leads-the-charge-for-tipperary-233768.html|title=Hammersley leads the charge for Tipperary|date=10 June 2013|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Jackie|last=Cahill}}</ref> He won a [[Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|Munster Championship]] medal on 19 July 2013 following a 0-19 to 0-18 defeat of Cork in the [[2011 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship#Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|Munster final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/tipp-heap-more-misery-on-cork-237435.html|title=Tipp heap more misery on Cork|date=20 July 2013|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Diarmuid|last=O'Flynn}}</ref> On 31 August 2013, O'Brien lined out at right corner-back when Tipperary faced [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] in the [[All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship|All-Ireland final]]. He ended the game with a winners' medal following the 2-14 to 2-11 victory.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/hurling/tipp-shake-off-plucky-cats-241717.html|title=Tipp shake off plucky Cats|date=2 September 2013|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=John|last=Knox}}</ref>\n\nO'Brien was once again included on the intermediate team for the [[2015 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship#Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|2015 Munster Championship]]. He played his last game in the grade on 21 June 2015 when he lined out at right corner-back in 1-23 to 2-13 defeat by [[Limerick GAA|Limerick]].\n\n====Senior====\n\nO'Brien was added to the Tipperary senior team in advance of the [[2017 National Hurling League|2017 National League]]. He was an unused substitute on 23 April 2017 when Tipperary suffered a 3-21 to 0-14 defeat by Galway in the [[2017 National Hurling League#Final|National League final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/2017/0423/869627-galway-v-tipperary/|title=Clinical Galway leave Tipp reeling in league final|date=23 April 2017|publisher=RT\u00c9 Sport|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Darragh|last=Small}}</ref> O'Brien made his first appearance for the team on 22 July when he came on as a 45th-minute substitute for James Barry in a 0-28 to 3-16 defeat of Clare in the [[2017 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship#All-Ireland Quarter-Finals|All-Ireland quarter-final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/sport/tipperary-have-beaten-clare-in-a-dramatic-all-ireland-shc-quarter-final-799029.html|title= Tipperary have beaten Clare in a dramatic All-Ireland SHC quarter final|date=24 July 2017|publisher=Irish Exminer|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n{{updated|match played 16 June 2019.}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Year\n!colspan=\"3\"|[[National Hurling League|National League]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Munster Senior Hurling Championship|Munster]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|All-Ireland]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Score!!Apps!!Score!!Apps!!Score!!Apps!!Score\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n|2017\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[National Hurling League|Division 1A]]\n|0||0-00||0||0-00||1||0-01||1||0-00\n|-\n|2018\n|5||0-00||4||0-00||colspan=2|\u2014||9||0-00\n|-\n|2019\n|0||0-00||2||0-00||1||0-00||3||0-00\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!5!!0-00!!6!!0-00!!2!!0-01!!13!!0-01\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n;Newport\n*[[Tipperary Intermediate Hurling Championship]] (1): 2016 (c)\n\n;Tipperary\n*[[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship]] (1): [[2019 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2019]]\n*[[All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship]] (1): [[2013 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship|2013]]\n*[[Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship]] (1): [[2013 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship#Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|2013]]\n*[[All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship]] (1): [[2010 All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship|2010]]\n*[[Munster Under-21 Hurling Championship]] (1): [[2010 All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship#Munster Under-21 Hurling Championship|2010]]\n*[[All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship]] (1): [[2007 All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship|2007]]\n*[[Munster Minor Hurling Championship]] (1): [[2007 All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship#Munster Minor Hurling Championship|2007]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External link==\n\n*[https://tipperary.gaa.ie/players/sean-obrien/ Se\u00e1n O'Brien profile] at the Tipperary GAA website\n\n{{Navboxes|title=Se\u00e1n O'Brien navigation boxes\n|list1=\n{{Tipperary Minor Hurling Team 2007}}\n{{Tipperary Under-21 Hurling Team 2010}}\n{{Tipperary Intermediate Hurling Team 2013}}\n{{Tipperary Hurling Team 2019}}\n}}\n{{Tipperary Hurling Team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:OBrien, Sean}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Newport hurlers]]\n[[Category:Tipperary inter-county hurlers]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox GAA player\n|image           =\n|name            = Sean O'Brien \n|irish           = Se\u00e1n \u00d3 Briain\n|nickname        =\n|occupation      = Engineer\n|height          =\n|sport           = Hurling\n|code            = Hurling\n|county          = Tipperary\n|province        = Munster\n|club            = [[Newport GAA|Newport]]\n|clyears         = \n|clposition      = Corner back\n|clapps(points)  =\n|clcounty        = 0\n|clprovince      =\n|clallireland    =\n|colleges        = [[University of Limerick]]\n|fitz            = 0\n|colyears        = 2007-2012\n|counties        = [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n|icyears         = 2017\u2013present\n|icposition      = Left corner-back\n|icapps(points)  = 7 (0-01)\n|icprovince      = 0\n|icallireland    = 1\n\n|nhl             = 0\n|allstars        = 0\n|clupdate        =\n|icupdate        = 10:37, 19 June 2019\n| birth_date= 1990\n| birth_place=[[Newport, County Tipperary|Newport]], [[County Tipperary]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n}}\n'''Sean O'Brien ''' (born 1990) is an Irish [[hurling|hurler]] who plays for Tipperary Championship club [[Newport GAA|Newport]] and at inter-county level with the [[Tipperary senior hurling team]]. He usually lines out as a left corner-back.\n\n==Playing career==\n===University of Limerick===\n\nO'Brien studied at the [[University of Limerick]] between 2007 and 2012 and joined the senior hurling team in his second year. He was a regular playedin several [[Fitzgibbon Cup]] campaigns with the university.\n\n===Newport===\n\nO'Brien joined the [[Newport GAA|Newport]] club at a young age and played in all grades at juvenile and underage levels. He eventually joined the club's top adult team in the [[Tipperary Intermediate Hurling Championship|Tipperary Intermediate Championship]].\n\nOn 23 October 2016, O'Brien captained Newport in the Tipperary Intermediate Championship final against [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]]. He ended the game with a winners' medal following the 1-17 to 0-15 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/newport-more-than-a-team-this-is-a-family-436795.html|title=Newport: More than a team \u2014 this is a family|publisher=Irish Examiner|date=28 December 2016|accessdate=18 June 2019|first=Larry|last=Ryan}}</ref>\n\n===Tipperary===\n====Minor and under-21====\n\nO'Brien first played for [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] when he joined the minor team in advance of the [[2007 All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship#Munster Minor Hurling Championship|2007 Munster Championship]]. He made his first appearance for the team on 2 May 2007 when he lined out at right corner-back in a 3-12 to 1-11 defeat of [[Clare GAA|Clare]]. O'Brien was switched to left corner-back when Tipperary faced [[Cork GAA|Cork]] in the [[Munster Minor Hurling Championship|Munster final]] on 8 July 2007. He ended the game with a winners' medal following the 0-18 to 1-11 victory. On 2 September 2007, O'Brien won an [[All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship|All-Ireland]] medal from left corner-back following Tipperary's 4-14 to 2-11 defeat of Cork in the [[2007 All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship#All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship|All-Ireland final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/hurling/carey-fires-tipperary-to-double-minor-glory-26315499.html|title=Carey fires Tipperary to double minor glory|date=3 September 2007|publisher=Irish Independent|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=|last=}}</ref>\n\nO'Brien was again eligible for the Tipperary minor team in [[2008 All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship#Munster Minor Hurling Championship|2008]]. He was an unused substitute when Tipperary suffered a 0-19 to 0-18 defeat by Cork in the Munster final on 13 July 2008.\n\nO'Brien was drafted onto the Tipperary under-21 team for the [[2010 All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship#Munster Under-21 Hurling Championship|2010 Munster Championship]]. He won a [[Munster Under-21 Hurling Championship|Munster Championship]] medal as a non-playing substitute on 28 July 2010 following Tipperary's 1-22 to 0-17 defeat of Cork in the final.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/tipp-take-another-step-forward-126466.html|title=Tipp take another step forward|date=29 June 2010|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Fintan|last=O'Toole}}</ref> On 11 September 2010, O'Brien won an [[All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship|All-Ireland]] medal from the substitutes' bench following Tipperary's 5-22 to 0-12 defeat of [[Galway GAA|Galway]] in the [[2010 All-Ireland Under-21 Hurling Championship Final|All-Ireland final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/hurling/fivestar-tipp-cruise-to-title-26680149.html|title=Five-star Tipp cruise to title|date=12 September 2010|publisher=Irish Independent|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Damian|last=Lawlor}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 June 2011, O'Brien made his first appearance for the Tipperary under-21 team when he came on as a substitute for [[James Barry (hurler)|James Barry]] at centre-back in a 4-12 to 1-16 defeat of [[Waterford GAA|Waterford]]. He was switched to left corner-back for the 4-19 to 1-21 defeat by Cork on 15 July 2011.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/awesome-rebel-firepower-161308.html|title=Awesome Rebel firepower|date=16 July 2011|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Fintan|last=O'Toole}}</ref>\n\n====Intermediate====\n\nO'Brien was added to the Tipperary intermediate panel for the [[2010 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship#Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|2010 Munster Championship]]. He was an unused substitute on 30 May 2010 when Tipperary suffered a 1-18 to 1-12 defeat by Cork at the quarter-final stage.\n\nOn 9 June 2013, O'Brien made his first appearance for the intermediate team when he lined out at right corner-back in a 0-20 to 0-15 defeat of Cork.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/hammersley-leads-the-charge-for-tipperary-233768.html|title=Hammersley leads the charge for Tipperary|date=10 June 2013|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Jackie|last=Cahill}}</ref> He won a [[Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|Munster Championship]] medal on 19 July 2013 following a 0-19 to 0-18 defeat of Cork in the [[2011 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship#Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|Munster final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/tipp-heap-more-misery-on-cork-237435.html|title=Tipp heap more misery on Cork|date=20 July 2013|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Diarmuid|last=O'Flynn}}</ref> On 31 August 2013, O'Brien lined out at right corner-back when Tipperary faced [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] in the [[All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship|All-Ireland final]]. He ended the game with a winners' medal following the 2-14 to 2-11 victory.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/hurling/tipp-shake-off-plucky-cats-241717.html|title=Tipp shake off plucky Cats|date=2 September 2013|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=John|last=Knox}}</ref>\n\nO'Brien was once again included on the intermediate team for the [[2015 All-Ireland Intermediate Hurling Championship#Munster Intermediate Hurling Championship|2015 Munster Championship]]. He played his last game in the grade on 21 June 2015 when he lined out at right corner-back in 1-23 to 2-13 defeat by [[Limerick GAA|Limerick]].\n\n====Senior====\n\nO'Brien was added to the Tipperary senior team in advance of the [[2017 National Hurling League|2017 National League]]. He was an unused substitute on 23 April 2017 when Tipperary suffered a 3-21 to 0-14 defeat by Galway in the [[2017 National Hurling League#Final|National League final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/2017/0423/869627-galway-v-tipperary/|title=Clinical Galway leave Tipp reeling in league final|date=23 April 2017|publisher=RT\u00c9 Sport|accessdate=12 June 2019|first=Darragh|last=Small}}</ref> O'Brien made his first appearance for the team on 22 July when he came on as a 45th-minute substitute for James Barry in a 0-28 to 3-16 defeat of Clare in the [[2017 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship#All-Ireland Quarter-Finals|All-Ireland quarter-final]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/sport/tipperary-have-beaten-clare-in-a-dramatic-all-ireland-shc-quarter-final-799029.html|title= Tipperary have beaten Clare in a dramatic All-Ireland SHC quarter final|date=24 July 2017|publisher=Irish Exminer|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n{{updated|match played 16 June 2019.}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Year\n!colspan=\"3\"|[[National Hurling League|National League]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Munster Senior Hurling Championship|Munster]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Cham