\n\n==History==\nRaetia's first game was played in December 2011 against the [[Chagos Islands national football team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chagossupport.org.uk/chagos-footballers-to-play-swiss-team-in-friendly-match-1863 |title=Chagos footballers to play Swiss team in friendly match |publisher=Chagossupport.org.uk |date=2011-11-28 |accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.suedostschweiz.ch/vermischtes/fa-ratia-verliert-ohne-gimma |title=Vermischtes: FA R\u00e4tia verliert ohne Gimma |publisher=Suedostschweiz.ch |date= |accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref> The second game took place in January 2012 on the island of Gozo against Gozo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gfa.com.mt/Match_Report_Gozo_Vs_FCRatia_part_1.html |title=Gozo Vs FA Ratia |publisher=Gfa.com.mt |accessdate=2012-08-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224055558/http://www.gfa.com.mt/Match_Report_Gozo_Vs_FCRatia_part_1.html |archivedate=24 February 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://footy-fever.com/blog/2013-african-cup-of-nations-qualifiers-stps-mystery-surprise/ |title=2013 African Cup of Nations Qualifiers: STP\u2019s Mystery & Surprise |publisher=Footy-fever.com |accessdate=2012-08-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502163323/http://footy-fever.com/blog/2013-african-cup-of-nations-qualifiers-stps-mystery-surprise/ |archivedate=2 May 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe first home game was on 26 May 2012 against the fifth Team of FC St. Pauli in [[Domat/Ems]] and Raetia won 6\u20130.\n\nRaetia was qualified to play the [[2012 VIVA World Cup]] in the northern Iraqi region of Kurdistan. In the group matches they gained a victory against Tamil Eelam and a loss to Zanzibar the 2nd rank and missed the semi-finals only because of goal difference.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.20min.ch/sport/fussball/story/27197631 |title=20 Minuten Online - \"Das Swat-Team auf der Trib\u00fcne war belustigend\" - Fussball |publisher=20min.ch |date= |accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.20min.ch/sport/fussball/story/22206569 |title=20 Minuten Online - Schweizer Kicker k\u00e4mpften im Irak - Fussball |publisher=20min.ch |date= |accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 September 2015 Raetia beat [[Franconia]] 6\u20130 and qualified for the [[2016 ConIFA World Football Cup]] in Abkhazia.\n\n==National Anthem==\nThe National Anthem of Raetia is \"A Tgalaveina\":<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ingeb.org/Lieder/udisilcl.html |title=A Tgalaveina / Udis il clom en la vallada free midi mp3 download Strand Hotel Sechelt bed breakfast |publisher=Ingeb.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref>\n\nUdis il clom en la vallada? <br />\nSi, si vus umens dils cumins! <br />\nLa libertad el smanatschada, <br />\nIgl inimitg ei sils confins. <br />\n<br />\nRefrain: <br />\nFontana muoss'a nus la via atras<br />\nIls flugs //dils battagliuns//.<br />\nPlitost la mort che sclaveria<br />\nEi la parola dils Grischuns.\n\n==Players & Manager==\n\n===Manager===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Nationality\n! Name\n|-\n| 2011\n| {{Flag icon|SUI}}\n|Rudolf Schmid\n|-\n| 2011\u20132012\n| {{Flag icon|SUI}}\n|Gian-Marco Schmid\n|-\n| 2012\n| {{Flag icon|SUI}}\n|Ursin Caviezel\n|-\n| 2012\u20132014\n| {{Flag icon|SUI}}\n| Costatino Demenga\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| {{Flag icon|SUI}} {{Flag icon|Kosovo}}\n| Arsim Ramizi\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n| {{Flag icon|SUI}} {{Flag icon|CRO}}\n| Alen Bratelj\n|-\n| 2016\u20132017\n| {{Flag icon|SUI}}\n| Pascal Amrein\n|-\n| 2017\u2013present\n| {{Flag icon|SUI}} \n| Aziz Agirman\n|}\n\n==Competitive record==\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break|width=40%}}\n\n===VIVA World Cup===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=9|[[VIVA World Cup|VIVA World Cup Record]]\n|-\n!Year\n!Round\n!Position\n!GP\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!GS\n!GA\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Occitania}} 2006\n|rowspan=4 colspan=8|''Did not qualify''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|S\u00e1pmi}} 2008\n|-\n|{{flagicon|P